Preheat oven to 425 degrees F. Combine soy sauce, molasses, garlic powder, and 1/2 teaspoon pepper; place mixture in bag and add chicken, turning to coat. Let stand 10 minutes (or overnight) to marinate. Toss fresh onions with oil, salt, and remaining 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Place onions in 13- x 9-inch baking dish; top with chicken. Bake 20-25 minutes or until chicken reaches 165 degrees F. Top chicken with crispy onions and cheese; bake 2-3 more minutes or until cheese melts. Combine both dressings; microwave on HIGH 20-30 seconds or until hot. Drizzle sauce over chicken and serve.